  "texts": [
    "Simply put, a company is owned by its shareholders, governed by the board of directors, and managed by the chief executive officer (CEO) and other senior executives.",
    "For the purposes of this paper, the board of directors, which has a legal obligation to act in the best interest of the company (so-called \"fiduciary duties\"), seems particularly important.",
    "The board sets the company's strategic priorities, is responsible for risk oversight, and has significant influence over management (e.g., it can replace senior executives) [44,179].",
    "Boards typically delegate some of their most critical functions to specific board committees (e.g., the audit committee, risk committee, and compensation committee) [27,42,87].",
    "But since many members serve on several boards and only work part-time, they benefit from independent expert advice to fulfill their duties."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The board sets the company's strategic priorities, is responsible for risk oversight, and has significant influence over management (e.g., it can replace senior executives) [44,179].",
